===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|forlorn|lang=enm}}, {{term|forloren|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|forloren|lang=ang}} (past participle of {{m|ang|forlēosan||to lose}}), from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*fraluzanaz||lost}}, past participle of {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*fraleusaną||to lose}}, equivalent to {{prefix|for|lorn|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|verloren||lost|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|verloren||lost|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|förlorad||lost|lang=sv}}. More at {{l|en|lese}}/{{l|en|leese}}, {{l|en|lorn}}.

